The fundamentals of discrete probability theory will be treated. The language of set theory is needed to develop the theory. First defining events using sets, subsequently I will provide the explanation of probability measure, operations, independence of events, and so on. Bayes' rule that is important for prediction will be explained gradually. Basics of stochastic process will be delivered to discuss various phenomena. Those concepts will be explained with practical examples and directions to use.

";
